  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThere are assumptions some assumptions made about the minimum validator count (e.g., there is at least one validator for each slot per epoch).\r\n\r\nPresently we do not enforce a minimum validator count, we just don't spin up systems with too few validators. This works for testing, but will soon become frustrating. We should throw a major error (effectively a panic) if a chain is started without enough validators. \r\n",
